§<~>30<~>.<~>In<~>the<~>First<~>Book<~>the<~>world<~>was<~>explained<~>as<~>mere<~>idea<~>,<~>object<~>for<~>*NL*<~>a<~>subject<~>.<~>In<~>the<~>Second<~>Book<~>we<~>considered<~>it<~>from<~>its<~>other<~>side<~>,<~>and<~>*NL*<~>found<~>that<~>in<~>this<~>aspect<~>it<~>is<~>will<~>,<~>which<~>proved<~>to<~>be<~>simply<~>that<~>*NL*<~>which<~>this<~>world<~>is<~>besides<~>being<~>idea<~>.<~>In<~>accordance<~>with<~>this<~>knowledge<~>*NL*<~>we<~>called<~>the<~>world<~>as<~>idea<~>,<~>both<~>as<~>a<~>whole<~>and<~>in<~>its<~>parts<~>,<~>the<~>*NL*<~>objectification<~>of<~>will<~>,<~>which<~>therefore<~>means<~>the<~>will<~>become<~>object<~>,<~>*NL*<~>i.e.<~>,<~>idea<~>.<~>Further<~>,<~>we<~>remember<~>that<~>this<~>objectification<~>of<~>will<~>was<~>*NL*<~>found<~>to<~>have<~>many<~>definite<~>grades<~>,<~>in<~>which<~>,<~>with<~>gradually<~>increasing<~>*NL*<~>distinctness<~>and<~>completeness<~>,<~>the<~>nature<~>of<~>will<~>appears<~>in<~>the<~>idea<~>,<~>*NL*<~>that<~>is<~>to<~>say<~>,<~>presents<~>itself<~>as<~>object<~>.<~>In<~>these<~>grades<~>we<~>already<~>*NL*<~>recognised<~>the<~>Platonic<~>Ideas<~>,<~>for<~>the<~>grades<~>are<~>just<~>the<~>determined<~>*NL*<~>species<~>,<~>or<~>the<~>original<~>unchanging<~>forms<~>and<~>qualities<~>of<~>all<~>natural<~>*NL*<~>bodies<~>,<~>both<~>organised<~>and<~>unorganised<~>,<~>and<~>also<~>the<~>general<~>forces<~>which<~>*NL*<~>reveal<~>themselves<~>according<~>to<~>natural<~>laws<~>.<~>These<~>Ideas<~>,<~>then<~>,<~>as<~>a<~>whole<~>*NL*<~>express<~>themselves<~>in<~>innumerable<~>individuals<~>and<~>particulars<~>,<~>and<~>are<~>*NL*<~>related<~>to<~>these<~>as<~>archetypes<~>to<~>their<~>copies<~>.<~>The<~>multiplicity<~>of<~>such<~>*NL*<~>individuals<~>is<~>only<~>conceivable<~>through<~>time<~>and<~>space<~>,<~>their<~>appearing<~>*NL*<~>and<~>passing<~>away<~>through<~>causality<~>,<~>and<~>in<~>all<~>these<~>forms<~>we<~>recognise<~>*NL*<~>merely<~>the<~>different<~>modes<~>of<~>the<~>principle<~>of<~>sufficient<~>reason<~>,<~>which<~>is<~>*NL*<~>the<~>ultimate<~>principle<~>of<~>all<~>that<~>is<~>finite<~>,<~>of<~>all<~>individual<~>existence<~>,<~>*NL*<~>and<~>the<~>universal<~>form<~>of<~>the<~>idea<~>as<~>it<~>appears<~>in<~>the<~>knowledge<~>of<~>the<~>*NL*<~>individual<~>as<~>such<~>.<~>The<~>Platonic<~>Idea<~>,<~>on<~>the<~>other<~>hand<~>,<~>does<~>not<~>come<~>*NL*<~>under<~>this<~>principle<~>,<~>and<~>has<~>therefore<~>neither<~>multiplicity<~>nor<~>change<~>.<~>*NL*<~>While<~>the<~>individuals<~>in<~>which<~>it<~>expresses<~>itself<~>are<~>innumerable<~>,<~>and<~>*NL*<~>unceasingly<~>come<~>into<~>being<~>and<~>pass<~>away<~>,<~>it<~>remains<~>unchanged<~>as<~>one<~>and<~>*NL*<~>the<~>same<~>,<~>and<~>the<~>principle<~>of<~>sufficient<~>reason<~>has<~>for<~>it<~>no<~>meaning<~>.<~>*NL*<~>As<~>,<~>however<~>,<~>this<~>is<~>the<~>form<~>under<~>which<~>all<~>knowledge<~>of<~>the<~>subject<~>*NL*<~>comes<~>,<~>so<~>far<~>as<~>the<~>subject<~>knows<~>as<~>an<~>individual<~>,<~>the<~>Ideas<~>lie<~>quite<~>*NL*<~>outside<~>the<~>sphere<~>of<~>its<~>knowledge<~>.<~>If<~>,<~>therefore<~>,<~>the<~>Ideas<~>are<~>to<~>*NL*<~>become<~>objects<~>of<~>knowledge<~>,<~>this<~>can<~>only<~>happen<~>by<~>transcending<~>the<~>*NL*<~>individuality<~>of<~>the<~>knowing<~>subject<~>.<~>The<~>more<~>exact<~>and<~>detailed<~>*NL*<~>explanation<~>of<~>this<~>is<~>what<~>will<~>now<~>occupy<~>our<~>attention<~>.<~>*NL*<~>*NL*<~>§<~>31<~>.<~>First<~>,<~>however<~>,<~>the<~>following<~>very<~>essential<~>remark<~>.<~>I<~>hope<~>that<~>in<~>*NL*<~>the<~>preceding<~>book<~>I<~>have<~>succeeded<~>in<~>producing<~>the<~>conviction<~>that<~>what<~>*NL*<~>is<~>called<~>in<~>the<~>Kantian<~>philosophy<~>the<~>thing-in-itself<~>,<~>and<~>appears<~>*NL*<~>there<~>as<~>so<~>significant<~>,<~>and<~>yet<~>so<~>obscure<~>and<~>paradoxical<~>a<~>doctrine<~>,<~>*NL*<~>and<~>especially<~>on<~>account<~>of<~>the<~>manner<~>in<~>which<~>Kant<~>introduced<~>it<~>as<~>an<~>*NL*<~>inference<~>from<~>the<