<~>the<~>*NL*<~>treatment<~>of<~>tragedy<~>.<~>The<~>representation<~>of<~>a<~>great<~>misfortune<~>is<~>alone<~>*NL*<~>essential<~>to<~>tragedy<~>.<~>But<~>the<~>many<~>different<~>ways<~>in<~>which<~>this<~>is<~>*NL*<~>introduced<~>by<~>the<~>poet<~>may<~>be<~>brought<~>under<~>three<~>specific<~>conceptions<~>.<~>It<~>*NL*<~>may<~>happen<~>by<~>means<~>of<~>a<~>character<~>of<~>extraordinary<~>wickedness<~>,<~>touching<~>*NL*<~>the<~>utmost<~>limits<~>of<~>possibility<~>,<~>who<~>becomes<~>the<~>author<~>of<~>the<~>*NL*<~>misfortune<~>;<~>examples<~>of<~>this<~>kind<~>are<~>Richard<~>III.<~>,<~>Iago<~>in<~>``<~>Othello<~>,<~>''<~>*NL*<~>Shylock<~>in<~>``<~>The<~>Merchant<~>of<~>Venice<~>,<~>''<~>Franz<~>Moor<~>,<~>Phædra<~>of<~>Euripides<~>,<~>*NL*<~>Creon<~>in<~>the<~>``<~>Antigone<~>,<~>''<~>&<~>c.<~>,<~>&<~>c.<~>Secondly<~>,<~>it<~>may<~>happen<~>through<~>blind<~>*NL*<~>fate<~>,<~>i.e.<~>,<~>chance<~>and<~>error<~>;<~>a<~>true<~>pattern<~>of<~>this<~>kind<~>is<~>the<~>Œdipus<~>*NL*<~>Rex<~>of<~>Sophocles<~>,<~>the<~>``<~>Trachiniæ<~>''<~>also<~>;<~>and<~>in<~>general<~>most<~>of<~>the<~>*NL*<~>tragedies<~>of<~>the<~>ancients<~>belong<~>to<~>this<~>class<~>.<~>Among<~>modern<~>tragedies<~>,<~>*NL*<~>``<~>Romeo<~>and<~>Juliet<~>,<~>''<~>``<~>Tancred<~>''<~>by<~>Voltaire<~>,<~>and<~>``<~>The<~>Bride<~>of<~>Messina<~>,<~>''<~>are<~>*NL*<~>examples<~>.<~>Lastly<~>,<~>the<~>misfortune<~>may<~>be<~>brought<~>about<~>by<~>the<~>mere<~>position<~>*NL*<~>of<~>the<~>dramatis<~>personæ<~>with<~>regard<~>to<~>each<~>other<~>,<~>through<~>their<~>*NL*<~>relations<~>;<~>so<~>that<~>there<~>is<~>no<~>need<~>either<~>for<~>a<~>tremendous<~>error<~>or<~>an<~>*NL*<~>unheard-of<~>accident<~>,<~>nor<~>yet<~>for<~>a<~>character<~>whose<~>wickedness<~>reaches<~>the<~>*NL*<~>limits<~>of<~>human<~>possibility<~>;<~>but<~>characters<~>of<~>ordinary<~>morality<~>,<~>under<~>*NL*<~>circumstances<~>such<~>as<~>often<~>occur<~>,<~>are<~>so<~>situated<~>with<~>regard<~>to<~>each<~>*NL*<~>o